/**
 * @page topic_build CMake Compile README
 * @ingroup build
 * @brief CMake-based build system with cross-platform support and modular architecture
 *
 * @section build_overview Overview
 *
 * ascii-chat uses a highly modular CMake build system designed for cross-platform
 * development across Linux, macOS, and Windows. The build system automatically
 * handles platform differences, dependency management, caching, and optimization
 * for both development and release builds.
 *
 * **Key Features**:
 * - Modular CMake architecture (30+ specialized modules)
 * - Cross-platform support (Linux, macOS, Windows)
 * - Automatic dependency caching (ccache, FetchContent)
 * - Multiple build types (Debug, Dev, Release, RelWithDebInfo, Coverage)
 * - Static release builds with musl (Linux only)
 * - High-performance allocator (mimalloc) for release builds
 * - CMake presets for common configurations
 * - Windows build script for convenience
 *
 * @section build_requirements Build Tool Requirements
 *
 * ascii-chat requires various build tools beyond just the compiler and CMake.
 * This section documents **all** external commands and utilities needed for building,
 * testing, and packaging the project.
 *
 * **Note**: This section covers **build tools only**. For library dependencies
 * (zstd, libsodium, PortAudio, etc.), see @ref topic_dependencies.
 *
 * @subsection build_requirements_core Core Build Tools
 *
 * **Required for All Builds**:
 *
 * | Tool | Purpose | Minimum Version | Where Used |
 * |------|---------|-----------------|------------|
 * | **cmake** | Build system generator | 3.16+ | Configure and generate build files |
 * | **clang** | C compiler (primary) | 10+ | Compile C source files |
 * | **ninja** or **make** | Build executor | Any | Execute build commands |
 * | **ar** | Static library archiver | Any | Create .a static libraries |
 * | **ranlib** | Static library indexer | Any | Index .a static libraries |
 *
 * **Alternative Archivers** (used by LLVM toolchain):
 * | Tool | Purpose | Where Used |
 * |------|---------|------------|
 * | **llvm-ar** | LLVM static library archiver | musl builds, LLVM toolchain |
 * | **llvm-ranlib** | LLVM static library indexer | musl builds, LLVM toolchain |
 * | **llvm-lib** | LLVM library tool (Windows) | Windows Clang builds (BearSSL) |
 *
 * On most systems, `ar` and `ranlib` are provided by:
 * - **Linux**: GNU Binutils or LLVM
 * - **macOS**: Xcode Command Line Tools (Apple's ar/ranlib)
 * - **Windows**: LLVM (llvm-ar, llvm-ranlib, llvm-lib) or MinGW (ar, ranlib)
 *
 * @subsection build_requirements_llvm LLVM Toolchain Configuration
 *
 * **LLVM Tools** (for advanced builds and musl):
 *
 * | Tool | Purpose | Where Used | Required For |
 * |------|---------|------------|--------------|
 * | **llvm-config** | Query LLVM configuration | LLVM.cmake | Homebrew LLVM, musl builds |
 * | **llvm-ar** | LLVM static archiver | LLVM.cmake | musl builds (alternative to ar) |
 * | **llvm-ranlib** | LLVM library indexer | LLVM.cmake | musl builds (alternative to ranlib) |
 * | **llvm-symbolizer** | Symbolize stack traces | Sanitizer builds | Better ASan/UBSan output |
 * | **llvm-profdata** | Profile data tool | Coverage builds | Generate coverage data |
 * | **llvm-cov** | Coverage visualization | Coverage builds | HTML coverage reports |
 *
 * **llvm-config Usage**:
 * - Queries LLVM installation paths and version
 * - Used to detect LLVM toolchain on Homebrew (macOS)
 * - Provides library paths for linking
 * - Not required for basic builds (only Homebrew LLVM)
 *
 * @code{.bash}
 * # Check llvm-config availability
 * llvm-config --version
 *
 * # Show LLVM installation prefix
 * llvm-config --prefix
 *
 * # Show LLVM library directory
 * llvm-config --libdir
 * @endcode
 *
 * @subsection build_requirements_linker Linker Tools
 *
 * **Linker Selection** (platform-specific):
 *
 * | Tool | Purpose | Platform | When Used |
 * |------|---------|----------|-----------|
 * | **lld** | LLVM linker | Linux | musl static builds (via `-fuse-ld=lld`) |
 * | **ld** | GNU linker | Linux | glibc builds (default) |
 * | **lld-link** | LLVM linker (Windows) | Windows | Clang builds (default) |
 * | **link.exe** | MSVC linker | Windows | MSVC builds |
 *
 * The build system automatically selects the appropriate linker based on:
 * - Compiler toolchain (Clang prefers lld)
 * - Build type (musl requires lld for static-PIE)
 * - Platform (Windows uses lld-link or link.exe)
 *
 * @subsection build_requirements_binary Binary Analysis Tools
 *
 * **Optional but Recommended**:
 *
 * | Tool | Purpose | Where Used | Required For |
 * |------|---------|------------|--------------|
 * | **strip** | Remove debug symbols | PostBuild.cmake | Release stripping (optional) |
 * | **objcopy** | Copy/modify object files | PostBuild.cmake | Debug info extraction (optional) |
 * | **ldd** | Show dynamic dependencies | Manual verification | Verify static linking |
 * | **file** | Identify file types | Manual verification | Check binary format |
 * | **nm** | List symbol table | Debugging | Symbol analysis |
 * | **objdump** | Disassemble binaries | Debugging | Assembly inspection |
 * | **readelf** | Display ELF info | Debugging (Linux) | ELF header analysis |
 * | **dumpbin.exe** | Display PE info | Debugging (Windows) | PE header analysis |
 *
 * **Usage Examples**:
 * @code{.bash}
 * # Verify static linking (Linux)
 * ldd build/bin/ascii-chat
 * # Expected: "not a dynamic executable" for musl static builds
 *
 * # Check binary type
 * file build/bin/ascii-chat
 * # Expected: "ELF 64-bit LSB pie executable, statically linked"
 *
 * # List symbols
 * nm build/bin/ascii-chat | grep malloc
 * # Shows malloc implementation (mi_malloc for mimalloc builds)
 *
 * # Check shared library dependencies (non-static)
 * objdump -p build/bin/ascii-chat | grep NEEDED
 * # Lists dynamic libraries required
 * @endcode
 *
 * @subsection build_requirements_documentation Documentation Tools
 *
 * **For Building Documentation**:
 *
 * | Tool | Purpose | Required For | Notes |
 * |------|---------|--------------|-------|
 * | **doxygen** | Generate API docs | `docs` target, Release packages | **Required for releases** |
 * | **dot** (Graphviz) | Generate diagrams | Enhanced docs (optional) | Improves documentation |
 *
 * **Why Doxygen is Required for Releases**:
 * - Release packages (`make package`) **include documentation**
 * - Documentation includes HTML API reference and Unix manpages
 * - Manpages are generated by Doxygen and installed to `share/man/man3/`
 * - Without Doxygen, releases will be missing documentation files
 *
 * **Building Documentation**:
 * @code{.bash}
 * # Check if doxygen is available
 * doxygen --version
 *
 * # Build documentation
 * cmake --build build --target docs
 *
 * # Documentation output
 * ls build/docs/html/       # HTML documentation
 * ls build/docs/man/man3/   # Unix manpages
 *
 * # Build release package (includes documentation)
 * cmake --build build --target package
 * @endcode
 *
