 * @subsection build_requirements_windows Windows-Specific Requirements
 *
 * **Bash on Windows**:
 *
 * Windows builds require bash for running test scripts and certain build operations.
 * The build system automatically detects bash from common locations.
 *
 * **Recommended Bash Providers**:
 *
 * 1. **Git Bash** (Recommended):
 *    - Bundled with Git for Windows
 *    - Download: https://git-scm.com/download/win
 *    - Default location: `C:\Program Files\Git\usr\bin\bash.exe`
 *    - Automatically detected by CMake
 *
 * 2. **WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)**:
 *    - Full Linux environment on Windows
 *    - Install: `wsl --install` (PowerShell as admin)
 *    - Access: `wsl bash` or `bash.exe` (if in PATH)
 *    - Provides complete Unix toolset
 *
 * 3. **MSYS2**:
 *    - Unix-like environment for Windows
 *    - Download: https://www.msys2.org/
 *    - Includes bash, make, and other Unix tools
 *
 * **Detection and Configuration**:
 * @code{.cmake}
 * # CMake automatically searches for bash in:
 * # 1. C:/Program Files/Git/usr/bin/bash.exe  (Git Bash)
 * # 2. C:/Program Files/Git/bin/bash.exe      (Git Bash alternate)
 * # 3. bash.exe in PATH                        (WSL, MSYS2, etc.)
 * @endcode
