 * @subsection build_requirements_differences Platform Differences
 *
 * **Tool Availability by Platform**:
 *
 * | Tool Category | Linux | macOS | Windows |
 * |---------------|-------|-------|---------|
 * | **Compiler** | clang, gcc | clang (default) | clang, MSVC |
 * | **Build Tool** | ninja, make, gmake | ninja, make, gmake | ninja, nmake, MSBuild |
 * | **Archiver** | ar, llvm-ar | ar (Apple) | llvm-ar, llvm-lib |
 * | **Linker** | ld, lld | ld (Apple) | lld-link, link.exe |
 * | **Shell** | bash, sh, env | bash, sh | Git Bash, WSL, PowerShell, cmd |
 * | **Package** | dpkg, rpm, tar, zip | productbuild, tar | wix, makensis, zip (CMake) |
 * | **Debugger** | gdb, lldb, valgrind | lldb (default), leaks | lldb, Visual Studio |
 * | **LLVM Tools** | llvm-config, llvm-ar, llvm-ranlib | llvm-config, llvm-ar, llvm-ranlib | llvm-lib, llvm-ar, llvm-ranlib |
 * | **System Info** | nproc, date, xdg-open | sysctl, xcrun, open | wmic, start |
 * | **Pkg Config** | pkg-config (native) | pkg-config (Homebrew) | N/A (uses vcpkg) |
 * | **Version Control** | git | git | git |
 * | **Static Builds** | musl-gcc, gcc, lld | Limited (dynamic preferred) | vcpkg static triplet |
 *
 * **Key Differences**:
 *
 * 1. **Compiler Ecosystem**:
 *    - **Linux**: Flexible (GCC or Clang), but ascii-chat uses Clang
 *    - **macOS**: Clang is default (`gcc` often symlinks to clang)
 *    - **Windows**: Clang preferred (MSVC supported but not primary)
 *
 * 2. **Build Systems**:
 *    - **Linux/macOS**: Ninja (fast) or Make (traditional)
 *    - **Windows**: Ninja (recommended), NMake (MSVC), or MSBuild (Visual Studio)
 *
 * 3. **Binary Tools**:
 *    - **Linux**: Rich GNU Binutils (objdump, readelf, nm, etc.)
 *    - **macOS**: Apple tools (otool, dyldinfo, etc.) or LLVM tools
 *    - **Windows**: Limited (dumpbin.exe with Visual Studio, or LLVM tools)
 *
 * 4. **Static Linking**:
 *    - **Linux**: Excellent (musl libc fully static)
 *    - **macOS**: Limited (system libraries usually dynamic)
 *    - **Windows**: Good (static UCRT available with vcpkg)
 *
 * 5. **Package Managers**:
 *    - **Linux**: apt, dnf, pacman (native)
 *    - **macOS**: Homebrew (third-party but universal)
 *    - **Windows**: vcpkg (Microsoft), scoop, chocolatey
