 * @subsubsection build_requirements_debug Debug Build (CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug)
 *
 * **Purpose**: Development with sanitizers (ASan, UBSan) for catching bugs
 *
 * **Required Tools** (all platforms):
 * - **cmake** (3.16+)
 * - **clang** (10+) - compiler
 * - **ninja** or **make** - build executor
 * - **ar** and **ranlib** (or llvm-ar/llvm-ranlib) - static library tools
 * - System libraries: see @ref topic_dependencies
 *
 * **Required Tools** (platform-specific):
 * - **pkg-config** (Linux/macOS only) - finds dependency flags
 * - **bash** (Windows only) - Git Bash or WSL for test scripts
 * - **nproc** (Linux), **sysctl** (macOS), **wmic** (Windows) - CPU detection
 * - **date** (Unix) - build timing
 * - **powershell** (Windows) - build timing and scripts
 *
 * **Optional but Recommended**:
 * - **llvm-symbolizer** (all platforms) - symbolizes ASan/UBSan stack traces
 * - **addr2line** (all platforms) - alternative to llvm-symbolizer for backtraces
 * - **ccache** (all platforms) - 5-10x faster rebuilds
 * - **git** (all platforms) - version detection, dependency patching
 * - **lldb** or **gdb** (all platforms) - interactive debugging
 * - **valgrind** (Linux) or **leaks** (macOS) - additional memory checking
 *
 * **Not Needed**:
 * - lld, musl-gcc, doxygen, package tools - these are for release builds
