 * @subsection build_requirements_symbolizers Stack Trace Symbolizers
 *
 * **llvm-symbolizer vs addr2line**:
 *
 * Both tools convert addresses to source locations in stack traces:
 *
 * | Feature | llvm-symbolizer | addr2line |
 * |---------|-----------------|-----------|
 * | **Platform** | All (Linux, macOS, Windows) | All (Linux, macOS, Windows) |
 * | **Provider** | LLVM/Clang | GNU Binutils |
 * | **Speed** | Faster | Slower |
 * | **Accuracy** | Better with Clang | Better with GCC |
 * | **ASan/UBSan** | Preferred | Fallback |
 * | **Required** | No (optional) | No (optional) |
 *
 * **How Symbolizers Work**:
 * - Sanitizers (ASan, UBSan) print raw addresses by default
 * - Symbolizer converts addresses to `file:line:function` format
 * - Makes crash reports much more readable
 * - Works with debug symbols (`-g` flag)
 *
 * **Using Symbolizers**:
 * @code{.bash}
 * # Without symbolizer (raw addresses)
 * ./build/bin/ascii-chat
 * # Output: #0 0x7f8b9c3d4e20 in ?? ??:0
 *
 * # With llvm-symbolizer (readable)
 * export ASAN_SYMBOLIZER_PATH=/usr/bin/llvm-symbolizer
 * ./build/bin/ascii-chat
 * # Output: #0 0x7f8b9c3d4e20 in process_frame lib/image.c:123
 *
 * # With addr2line (alternative)
 * export ASAN_SYMBOLIZER_PATH=/usr/bin/addr2line
 * ./build/bin/ascii-chat
 * @endcode
 *
 * **Availability**:
 * - **llvm-symbolizer**: Comes with LLVM/Clang installation
 * - **addr2line**: Comes with GNU Binutils (gcc, ld, etc.)
 * - Both are **optional** - builds work without them
 * - Debug builds are **much more useful** with symbolizers
 *
